.TH mklost+found 8
.SH NAME
\*Lmklost+found\*O \- Makes a \*Llost\(plfound\*O directory for \*Lfsck\*O
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.sS 
\*Lmklost+found\*O
.sE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "mklost+found command"
.iX "lost and found directory"
.iX "directories" "lost and found"
.PP 
The \*Lmklost+found\*O command creates
a \*Llost+found\*O directory
in the current directory.  \*Lmklost+found\*O
also creates (and then removes) a number of empty files
so that there will be empty slots for \*Lfsck\*O.
The \*Lfsck\*O command reconnects any orphaned files and
directories by placing them in the \*Llost+found\*O directory with
an assigned inode number.
\*Lmklost+found\*O is not normally needed since \*Lnewfs\*O
automatically creates the \*Llost\(plfound\*O
directory when a new file system is created.
.SH FILES
.PP 
